                                    Challenge 3 : Event Driven Execution 


# so, whenever we make a workflow : it can be exectued in one of this two ways :

                        1. Sequential                                     2. Event Driven ( in case of complex agentic sysetm )

Langchain is not built for Event Driven Execution : never meant to stop execution in between the process .

### If we need to do it in LangChain ... so, this complete single long chain of recruitment process. needs to to break down into multiple small chains and the Event : is handled with help of external python GLUE code .
                        Ex : see, the JD is posted ---> waiting scipt with python ( 7 days ) --- > when this completes we 
                             must initiate next Chain .




While LangGraph provdes Event Driven Execution inherently. Here, since our execution is stateful .. and reaching on any particular 
node , we can store the current state : using LangGraph feature using Checkpoint and waiting for external Trigger. 



